From 598b04f0f7faa08e86b90422000146bb2d26cc7f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: shuka0158 <shukakidze.davit2010@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 15:35:37 +0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ARF Custom edition: port Flipper-ARF onto Momentum

- Port 31 automotive Sub-GHz protocols (VAG, PSA, Ford v0-v3, Kia v0-v7,
  BMW CAS4, Subaru, Mazda, Mitsubishi, Chrysler, Honda, Suzuki, Porsche,
  Land Rover, Fiat, scher_khan, sheriff_cfm, star_line) plus AUT64
  cipher helper and auto_rke_protocols/landrover_rke shared helpers.
- Port keeloq.c shifted-button mapping (Pandora/Suzuki/Nissan/DoorHan/
  Alligator/Pantera_XS/APS-1100 etc.) into Momentum's keeloq stack.
- Port SUBGHZ_CUSTOM_BTN_DEFINE_MAP macro and long-press/multi-page
  button helpers (used by StarLine/Scher-Khan and ported Ford protocols).
- Port furi_hal_crypto_aes128_ecb_encrypt/decrypt primitives (used by kia_v6).
- Replace boot-time dolphin animation with a 2.5s boot text scene
  showing 'ARF Custom edition.' / 'GitHub: shuka0158'.
- Update protocol_items registry + finalize SDK api_symbols.csv.
